**1. DO THE v4 FIXES (a)-(e) HOLD?**
(a) **HOLDS.** P5/P2 clearly separate immutable "snapshots of what one run found" from the live "dossier view" which surfaces newly discovered conflicts.
(b) **HOLDS.** §5 Rendering Contract is explicitly "scoped to claim-derived rendering" at creation/view time; "stored run report is thereafter an immutable artifact, displayed as-written."
(c) **HOLDS.** Terminology corrected in P1 and §6: "ingestion is unconditional; the gate is an automatic promotion policy."
(d) **HOLDS.** P7 adds the "Honest dependency" clause, admitting the "no open contradiction" check is "only as good as contradiction detection" and committing to caveats/audit backstops.
(e) **HOLDS.** §3 operationalizes success as the ratio of "trusted vs. provisional claims" and its growth over time, removing the v3 tautology.

**2. DID ANY v4 FIX REOPEN A PRIOR ISSUE or create a new contradiction?**
No. The precision fixes resolve the remaining collisions between immutability and live state.

**3. FINAL CALL**
**ADVANCE.** The document has reached structural and terminology convergence; remaining risks (claim identity, extraction quality) are properly deferred to the Feature/Architecture layers.

